                <expan><abbr>P</abbr><ex>ublius</ex></expan> Aelius Vita<lb break="no" n="2"/>lis <expan><abbr>an</abbr><ex>norum</ex></expan> XIII et <lb n="3"/><expan><abbr>P</abbr><ex>ublius</ex></expan> Aelius Vict<lb break="no" n="4"/>or <expan><abbr>an</abbr><ex>norum</ex></expan> I <expan><abbr>h</abbr><ex>ic</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>iti</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>unt</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>arcus</ex></expan> <lb n="5"/><expan><abbr>Ul</abbr><ex>pius</ex></expan> Ianuarius <lb n="6"/>fili<expan><ex>i</ex><abbr>s</abbr></expan> <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>osuit</ex></expan>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Oberhalb des Inschriftfeldes Büsten eines Mannes und eines Knaben. Z. 4: Altersangabe nur scheinbar ein L, dessen vermeintliche waagrechte Haste von einer Verletzung im Stein herrührt.</p>
